OL,5,Cshows
OL,7,FThough this new research shows the
OL,8,Fsuccess of diversion, it also sheds a
OL,9,Flight on how black children are 15%
OL,10,Fless likely to be given this choice.
OL,12,FBlack children also faced
OL,13,Fdisproportionately higher rates of
OL,14,Fpolice contact than children from
OL,15,Fother ethnic groups (making up 44.3%
OL,16,Fof all cases, despite only
OL,17,Frepresenting 24.7% of the local
OL,18,Fpopulation over the study period).
OL,20,FUnited Borders are joining calls for
OL,21,Fdiversion to be more widely offered.
